accessibility.text: massive star attempts to evolve redward
encounters the Humphreys-Davidson Limit beyond which no stable stars are observed
optically thick pseudo-photosphere forms at larger radius than hydrostatic stellar surface
mass loss, decrease in effective temp
pseudo-photosphere moves out (no expansion of star)
We emphasize however that neither -Car type nor S-Dor type variations are understood.
